	MC ADE
M.C. A.D.E. (born Adrian Hines in Miami, Florida) is an American music producer and rapper who helped pioneer the hip hop sub-genre of Miami bass music. His 1985 single, "Bass Rock Express", a collaboration with engineer Amos Larkins, is often considered to be the start of Miami Bass. Pappawheelie. "Miami Bass: The Primer". Stylus Magazine. Retrieved on December 4, 2009.  His single "Bass Mechanic" is also considered an example.   He recorded on the 4-Sight record label, which was owned by his father Billy Hines. His name stands for Adrian Does Everything, which refers to the fact that he both rapped and produced his own records. 
Discography

